revision.text:
'''Advanced Library Format''' (ALF), also known as '''IEEE 1603''' or '''IEC 62265''', is an [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers|IEEE]] and [[International Electrotechnical Commission|IEC]] standard that describes a data [[specification language]] for library elements used in [[ASIC]] design applications for [[integrated circuits]].  ALF can model behavior, timing, power and noise, hot electron, electromigration, antenna effects, physical abstraction and physical implementation rules of library elements.<ref>{{cite press release| title = IEEE Approves Advanced Library Format Standard for Integrated Circuit Design| publisher = The Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Standards Association| date = 15 October 2003|url=http://standards.ieee.org/announcements/pr_1603app.html| accessdate =13 June 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Roethig |first=Wolfgang | title=Advanced library format "attacks" advanced design issues|publisher=EE Times|date=13 January 2003|url=http://www.eetimes.com/story/OEG20030110S0035|accessdate =13 June 2007}}</ref>

