An '''optical mount''' is a device used to join a normal [[camera]] and another optical instrument, such as a [[microscope]] or [[telescope]]. The optical mount is generally attached to the camera as a [[camera lens|lens]] would on one end, and fastened to the other instrument in a similar fashion. Optical mounts are used extensively in [[science|scientific]] imaging applications in [[biology]] and [[astronomy]].

